<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><?xml-stylesheet href="\\Ameras0036\Data\BIEM_PRODUCTION_AMERICA\053_NJT\Application\p-xml\XSL\053_NJT_ib.xslt" type="text/xsl"?><!--thru 053_NJT_p-iem_IB.xslt--><ib miid="BOM01285" doc-type="MI" maint-item-desc="Passenger Emergency Intercom" part-number="05384090031S" doc-name="BOM01285_MI" doc-title="PEI" lock-counter="18" search-index="mim-sys9-dno" show-e-list="yes" e-list-number="09 01 03" giid-maint-item-desc="Passenger Emergency Intercom" id-document="21418" id-document-version="41244" doc-version="1" pmt-version="14" gmt-version="12" user-defined-1="" user-defined-2="" user-defined-3="" oem-part-no="" device-name="PEI"><maintenance-item><para reuse="all">The Passenger Emergency Intercom (PEI) panel
allows passenger to call the train crew by sounding a chime over
the public address loudspeakers, then communicate with the crew
member answering the call. </para><para reuse="all">PEI panel units are located throughout the car
(see Figure <ref-container><iref ref-id="CHDJFHHH"></iref></ref-container> and
Table <ref-container><iref ref-id="CHDCJDGA"></iref></ref-container>), mounted
in recessed openings in the wall liners. The unit weighs approximately
9 lb and measures approximately 13.8 in. high,
5.0 in. wide, and 4.0 in. deep. The panel face
is brushed stainless steel and the body is aluminum with a chemical
conversion coating. The labeling is engraved in the panel face and
permanently marked in black. Operating instructions are provided
next to the panel.</para><illustration reuse="all"><graphic file="..\..\Graphics\CGM\053J-751-009.cgm" cropped="1" float="0" height="5.70in" impsize="9.00in 5.70in"></graphic><title id="ID2008228215229294">Passenger Emergency Intercom</title></illustration><table frame="all" colsep="1" rowsep="1" reuse="all"><title id="CHDCJDGA">PEI Locations</title><tgroup cols="5" colsep="1" rowsep="1"><colspec colnum="1" colname="1" colwidth="1.125in"></colspec><colspec colnum="2" colname="2" colwidth="3.000in"></colspec><colspec colnum="3" colname="3" colwidth="0.375in"></colspec><colspec colnum="4" colname="4" colwidth="0.375in"></colspec><colspec colnum="5" colname="5" colwidth="0.375in"></colspec><thead><row rowsep="1"><entry colname="1" morerows="1" valign="middle">UNIT ID</entry><entry colname="2" morerows="1" valign="middle">LOCATION</entry><entry namest="3" nameend="5">QTY/CAR</entry></row><row rowsep="1"><entry colname="3">C</entry><entry colname="4">S</entry><entry colname="5">T</entry></row></thead><tbody><row rowsep="1"><entry colname="1" align="center">PEI1</entry><entry colname="2" align="left">A/F-end, Quarter Point Vestibule,
LS</entry><entry colname="3" align="center">1</entry><entry colname="4" align="center">1</entry><entry colname="5" align="center">1</entry></row><row rowsep="1"><entry colname="1" align="center">PEI2</entry><entry colname="2" align="left">A/F-end, Lower Level Partition,
LS</entry><entry colname="3" align="center">1</entry><entry colname="4" align="center">1</entry><entry colname="5" align="center">1</entry></row><row rowsep="1"><entry colname="1" align="center">PEI3</entry><entry colname="2" align="left">B-end, quarter point Vestibule,
RS</entry><entry colname="3" align="center">1</entry><entry colname="4" align="center">1</entry><entry colname="5" align="center">1</entry></row><row rowsep="1"><entry colname="1" align="center">PEI4</entry><entry colname="2" align="left">A/F-end, Upper Level Partition,
LS</entry><entry colname="3" align="center">1</entry><entry colname="4" align="center">1</entry><entry colname="5" align="center">1</entry></row><row rowsep="0"><entry colname="1" align="center">PEI5</entry><entry colname="2" align="left">B-end, Toilet Sidewall, LS</entry><entry colname="3" align="center">1</entry><entry colname="4" align="center">1</entry><entry colname="5" align="center">-</entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table><para reuse="all">The panel face is engraved with label text permanently
marked in black. A speaker, labeled <verbatim>EMERGENCY</verbatim>,
is mounted behind a grill punched at the top of the panel. A microphone
sits behind arrays of punched holes, just below the speaker. A placard
adjacent to the PEI provide operating instructions. A pushbutton
with a green/amber activity LED indicator, labeled <verbatim>PUSH
TO CALL</verbatim> (PTC), is mounted on the PEI front panel. </para><para reuse="all">A 3-plug car wiring cable connects to the PEI
14-pin connector. (See Table <ref-container><iref ref-id="CHDJABIB"></iref></ref-container>.) A ground wire connects
the PEI to the carbody. </para><table frame="all" colsep="1" rowsep="1" reuse="all"><title id="CHDJABIB">PEI Connections</title><tgroup cols="3" colsep="1" rowsep="1"><colspec colnum="1" colname="1" colwidth="1.125in"></colspec><colspec colnum="2" colname="2" colwidth="1.125in"></colspec><colspec colnum="3" colname="3" colwidth="4.750in"></colspec><thead><row rowsep="1"><entry colname="1">PLUG ID</entry><entry colname="2">PIN NO.</entry><entry colname="3">DESCRIPTION</entry></row></thead><tbody><row rowsep="1"><entry colname="1" align="center">GND</entry><entry colname="2" align="center">-</entry><entry colname="3">Carbody ground</entry></row><row rowsep="1"><entry colname="1" morerows="2" align="center">PA</entry><entry colname="2" align="center">1,2</entry><entry colname="3">Power (supplied by CCU)</entry></row><row rowsep="1"><entry colname="2" align="center">3</entry><entry colname="3">Discrete input for external pushbutton<para reuse="all">The input allows an External Push-to-call (EPTC)
pushbutton to replicate the functionality of the PTC pushbutton.
Only PEI5 (toilet) implements an EPTC pushbutton.</para></entry></row><row rowsep="1"><entry colname="2" align="center">4 - 6</entry><entry colname="3">Panel location and identification jumper pins</entry></row><row rowsep="1"><entry colname="1" align="center">PB</entry><entry colname="2" align="center">8 - 11</entry><entry colname="3">RS-485 Audio Control Network (shared by the
CCCP and all CCPs and PEIs)</entry></row><row rowsep="0"><entry colname="1" align="center">PC</entry><entry colname="2" align="center">12 - 14</entry><entry colname="3">Shared PEI audio signal (from CCU, one channel
shared by all PEIs)</entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table><para reuse="all">The External Push-to-call (EPTC) pushbutton
is simply a remote for the PEI5 (toilet) <verbatim>PUSH TO CALL</verbatim> pushbutton
and is located right below PEI5, on the toilet side wall. </para></maintenance-item></ib>